  "title": "Project Manager (Banking)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Manage end-to-end delivery of banking projects across initiation, planning, execution, monitoring, and closure</li></ul><ul><li><p>Work closely with business, operations, compliance, and IT teams to define project scope, timelines, and deliverables</p></li><li><p>Drive project governance, status reporting and stakeholder communication</p></li><li><p>Ensure adherence to banking regulations, risk controls, and internal governance standards</p></li><li><p>Manage project budgets, resource allocation, and vendor dependencies</p></li><li><p>Facilitate Agile ceremonies (if Agile) or manage Waterfall delivery as per project needs</p></li><li><p>Track and manage dependencies across multiple teams and systems</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely delivery with high quality and minimal risk</p></li><li><p>Support UAT planning, release coordination, and post-implementation reviews</p></li></ul><p>Required Skills & Experience</p><ul><li><p>7–8 years of overall experience in Project Management</p></li><li><p>Banking domain experience is mandatory </p></li><li><p>Experience managing technology and/or business transformation projects</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of SDLC, Agile and Waterfall methodologies</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with project tracking tools such as JIRA, MS Project, or similar</p></li><li><p>Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills</p></li></ul>",
